# preferred-citation points to the ZfdG article that references teiCrafter; it is
# a field survey rather than a paper solely about this software, used here per
# the maintainer's stated citation preference.
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use teiCrafter in academic work, please cite the preferred-citation
  (the ZfdG article). To cite the software itself, use the metadata below.
title: teiCrafter
abstract: >-
  A browser-based, client-only, lossless editor for arbitrary TEI-XML. The raw
  TEI string is canonical, edits are offset splices, and serialization is
  byte-identical outside the edit. An optional LLM on-ramp drafts initial TEI
  from plaintext; the model assists and the human decides.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Christopher
    family-names: Pollin
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4879-129X"
    affiliation: "Digital Humanities Craft OG"
repository-code: "https://github.com/DigitalHumanitiesCraft/teiCrafter"
url: "https://digitalhumanitiescraft.github.io/teiCrafter/"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - TEI
  - TEI-XML
  - digital scholarly editing
  - text encoding
  - lossless editing
  - human-in-the-loop
